or]]\n| Northeast = Hulu Kinta<br>[[Lojing]]\n| East      = [[Lojing]]<br>[[Cameron Highlands]]\n| Southeast = [[Simpang Pulai]]\n| South     = [[Batu Gajah]]\n| Southwest = [[Parit]]\n| West      = [[Manong, Perak|Manong]]\n| Northwest = [[Kuala Kangsar]]\n| Centre    = Ipoh\n}}\n{{Perak}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Articles related to Ipoh\n| list  = \n{{Cities in Malaysia}}\n{{Most populous cities in Malaysia}}\n{{Largest cities of Malaysia}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ipoh| ]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Perak]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1880]]\n[[Category:State capitals in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Cities in Malaysia]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the federal constituency formerly represented in the Dewan Rakyat|Ipoh (federal constituency)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{More citations needed|date=October 2011}}\n{{Advert|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Ipoh\n| settlement_type                 = [[List of cities in Malaysia|City]] and [[List of capitals in Malaysia|state capital]]\n| official_name                   = City of Ipoh<br>{{nobold|''Bandaraya Ipoh''}}\n| translit_lang1                  = Other\n| image_skyline                   = Ipoh composite.jpg\n| image_caption                   = Clockwise from top: Jalan Tun Sambanthan within the Old Town, [[Ipoh railway station|Railway Station]], City Hall, [[St. Michael's Institution]], Perak Tong Temple\n| image_flag                      = Flag of Ipoh, Perak.svg\n| flag_size                       = 115px\n| image_seal                      = Ipoh Emblem.svg\n| nickname                        = City of Millionaires, Bougainvillea City, Silver Valley\n| motto                           = Ipoh Bersih, Hijau dan Maju<br>\n({{lang-en|Ipoh Clean, Green and Progressive}})\n| image_map                       = {{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=shape|stroke-width=2|stroke-color=#000000|zoom=10|frame-lat=4.5972222222